TEXT71: Vehicle 1 traveling north on an undivided two-lane, two-way roadway approaching
an intersection, this intersection is control by a traffic signal.  Vehicle 2
traveling west on an undivided one-way, two-lane intersecting roadway controled
by a traffic signal, making a left turn.  Vehicle 1 applied the brakes with
lockup skidding longitudinally and steered left coming into contact with Vehicle
2 on the left side with the front.      No Air Bags deployed.  Vehicle 1 was
towed due to disabling damage.  Vehicle 2 was a non-tow.
Prior to this crash vehicle one was traveling east on an undivided two-lane,
two-way roadway while negotiating a right curve.  Vl started to rotate
clockwise, in the roadway, due to wet conditions.  V1 departed the roadway, on
the right side, down an embankment causing this vehicle to rollover
three-quarter turns, left side leading. During the rollover V1 struck a large
rock with its right side and came to final rest with its undercarriage striking
a 55cm tree.  V1 was towed due to disabling damage.  The driver of vehicle was
transported to a local medical facility via ambulance.
V2 was traveling south on a divided three-lane road in the right lane and
approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic signal.  V1 was also
traveling south on the same roadway behind V2.  The back of V2 was contacted by
the front of V1.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.  V1 was towed due
to damage.  V2 was not towed.  No occupants of either vehicle were transported.
It was raining, the road was wet and it was dawn at the time of the crash.  No
air bags deployed in V1.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve. The driver applied his brakes and V1 went off the left side of the road.
The vehicle climbed a steep embankment.  The left front of the vehicle swiped
the embankment.  V1 continued to climb the embankment and the left front tire
struck a large rock in the embankment.  V1 continued and started to descend the
embankment.  The left side of the vehicle swiped the embankment a second time.
The vehicle continued to descend the embankment and the front of V1 struck a 9
cm wide signpost.  V1 pushed the signpost over and came back on the roadway.
The signpost struck the right side of the vehicle.  V1 came to rest in the
roadway facing east.  V1 was towed due to damage.  The right front seat
passenger was transported due to injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was
dry, it was dark and the road was not lighted at the time of the crash.  No air
bags deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west, negotiating a right curve on an undivided
two-lane, two-way roadway.  Vehicle 1, lost control due to ice on roadway,
skidding clockwise, departed the roadway on the right side and struck an 18cm
wide tree with the left side of the vehicle.  No injuries to report.  Vehicle 1
was towed back onto the roadway and was driven away by occupant.  No air bags
deployed.  The road conditions were bituminous, curved right, level, with a
light layer of ice and during daylight hours.
V1 traveling south in the left lane of an undivided three-lane road approaching
an intersecting roadway to the left.  V2 was traveling north on a divided one
lane road negotiating a right curve and approaching the same intersection as V1.
The driver of V1 attempted to make a left turn at the intersection.  The front
of V1 struck the left side of V2.  V1 was propelled  backwards and the back of
V1 struck a guardrail off the west side of the roadway.  V1 came to rest against
the guardrail.  V2 rotated counterclockwise and went off the right side of the
road.  The right side of V2 struck a 7 cm wide delineator.  V2 continued and
came to rest off the right side of the road.  V1 was towed due to damage.  V2
was not towed.  No occupants of either vehicle were transported due to injuries.
The frontal air bags in V1 deployed.    The weather was clear, the road was
dry, it was dark and the road was lighted at the time of the crash.
V1 was stopped facing south on an undivided two-lane road waiting for on-coming
traffic to clear so as to make a left turn at an intersection.  V2 was traveling
south on the same undivided two-lane road to the rear of V1 and approaching the
same intersection as V1.  The front of V2 impacted the back of V1.  V2 came to
rest in the roadway.  V1 was propelled forward and came to rest on the
intersecting roadway.  Both vehicles were towed due to damage.  The driver of V1
and the driver of V2 were transported.  The frontal air bags in V2 deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west entering an intersection to make a left turn.
Vehicle 2 was traveling north entering the same intersection. V1's left and V2's
front impacted. Frontal air bags deployed in both vehicles.  Both vehicles were
towed due to disabling damage.  Occupant of Vehicle 1, transported to an area
hospital for treatment.  Occupant #2 of V2 was transported to an area hospital
for treatment.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided two-way, two-lane roadway.  Vehicle
l was negotiating a left curve in the roadway when the vehicle lost control due
to snow and ice .  Vehicle 1 started to rotate clockwise, departed roadway and
did strike a rock wall and shrubbery with the front right wheel of the vehicle.
Vehicle one then rolled over on to the left side. Vehicle 1 was towed due to
disabling damage.  No injuries to report.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane road.  V1 went off the
left side of the road.  The front of V1 struck a 26 cm diameter tree.  V1 came
to rest off the left side of the road.  V1 was towed due to damage.  The driver
was transported  to a medical facility for treatment of injuries.   The weather
was clear, the road was dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.  No
air bags deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided 4 lane two-way roadway coming to an
intersection control by a traffic light.  Vehicle 2 was traveling east on a 5
lane two-way roadway in the left turn lane that was also control by a traffic
light.  Vehicle 2 started to turn left at the intersection. The front of Vehicle
1 struck the right side of Vehicle 2.  No frontal air bags deployed, both
vehicle were towed due to disabling damage.  Occupant #3 in Vehicle 2 was
transported to area hospital.  Road conditions was dry, straight, and
bituminous.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve.  A deer entered the roadway from the west side of the road.  V1 struck
and killed the deer.  V1 came to rest in the roadway.  V1 was towed due to
damage.  No occupants of V1 were transported due to injuries.    No air bags
deployed.
V1 was going west negotiating a right curve in the roadway.  V1 departed the
roadway on the left side impacting a 30 cm tree with the front of the vehicle.
Driver of vehicle was injured and transported to the hospital.  V1 was towed due
to damage.
V1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane convenience store driveway.  V2
was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right curve and
approaching the driveway.  The driver of V1 attempted to make a left turn into
the two-lane roadway.  The left side of V1 and the front of V2 contacted.  V2
rotated counterclockwise and came to rest off the left side of the roadway.  V1
rotated slightly clockwise and continued across the two-lane roadway.  V1 went
off the west side of the road and the front of V1 struck a 28 cm diameter tree.
V1 came to rest off the roadway.  Both vehicles were towed due to damage.  The
driver of V1 was transported due to injuries.  No other occupants of V1 and no
occupants of V2 were transported.  The weather was clear, the road was dry and
it was daylight at the time of the crash.  The frontal air bags in V2 deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-way, two-lane roadway.
Vehicle 1 crossed over the left lane line, over corrected steering right and
departed the roadway on the right.  Vehicle 1 then started to rotate clockwise
and came in contact with two 12cm trees with the front of the vehicle.
Vehicle 1 was towed due to disabling vehicle damage.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road approaching an
intersection.  V2 was traveling west on the undivided two-lane intersecting
roadway which was controlled by a stop sign for V2.  V1 made a right turn at the
intersection and the front of V1 struck the front of V2.  Both vehicles were
towed due to damage.
Vehicle 1 was stopped in the center lane at a traffic signal facing north on a
divided three-lane roadway.  V2 was traveling north on the same three-lane
divided roadway in the center lane to the rear of V1.  The back of V1 was struck
by the front of V2.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.  V1 was towed
due to damage.  V2 was not towed.  The driver of V1 was transported to a medical
facility due to injuries.  It was cloudy, the road was dry and it was daylight
at the time of the crash.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane two-way roadway. Vehicle
2 was traveling east on an undivided two-lane two-way intersecting roadway,
slowing down for traffic when Vehicle 1 started to make a left turn to travel
west and struck vehicle 2 on the right front fender with the front of vehicle 1.
Both vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.  Air bags did not deploy.
No injuries to report.  Road conditions for both vehicles were dry, straight,
level, and bituminous and the weather was clear at the time.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a undivided two-lane two-way roadway.  V1 departed
the roadway on the left side. The front of Vehicle 1 impacted the downturned
end of a guardrail.  V1 mounted the guardrail and continued to travel east.  The
front of V1 impacted a sign post and continued to travel eastbound on the
guardrail causing undercarriage damage.  V1 then overturned to the left down a
steep embankment.  During the roll the undercarriage impacted with a tree.  V1
contuinued to roll and the front of the V1 impacted a two (2) additional trees.
The vehicle continued to roll and came to rest on its left side.  V1 was towed
due to damage.  The driver was transported due to injuries.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way, two-lane roadway when it departed its
travel lane and exited the road on the north side of travel. While off the
roadway, V1 sideswiped a tree with its right-side plane. V1 continued forward
until it struck another tree with its front-end plane. V1 came to final rest in
the immediate vicinity of this post secondary impact. V1 was towed from the
crash scene due to disabling damage. The operator of V1 was transported to a
local hospital via ambulance.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve on a steep downgrade.  V1 went off the left side of the road.  The front
of V1 struck a 5 cm wide tree and then the front of V1 struck a 19 cm wide tree.
V1 came to rest off the left side of the road.  V1 was towed due to damage.
The driver was transported due to injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was
dry, it was dark and the road was not lighted at the time of the crash.  The
frontal air bags deployed.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north and Vehicle #2 was traveling west on an
intersecting roadway.  The front of vehicle #1 impacted the left side of vehicle
#2, which caused the left side of vehicle #2 to sideslap the right side of
vehicle #1.  Vehicle #1 then departed the roadway impacting a 65cm tree with the
front of the vehicle.  Vehicle #2 rotated clockwise and departed the roadway on
the northwest corner and rolled over onto its left side with the top of the
vehicle impacting a 34cm pole.  Both vehicles were towed due to disabling
vehicle damage. Driver of vehicle #1 transported to area hospital.  Driver of
vehicle #2 expired at scene. Frontal air bags deployed in both vehicles.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve.  V1 went off the right side of the road.  The front of V1 struck a 20 cm
wide concrete post.  V1 continued to travel off the right side of the road and
the front of V1 swiped a 55 cm diameter tree.  V1 continued off the right side
of the road and the front of V1 struck a chain link fence, a 2 cm diameter metal
post and then a 1.3 meter diameter tree.  V1 came to rest off the right side of
the road.  V1 was towed due to damage.  The driver was transported due to
injuries.  It was cloudy, the road was dry, it was dark and the road was not
lighted at the time of the crash.  Both frontal air bags deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a right
curve on an upgrade.  V1 went off the right side of the road.  The vehicle
climbed a snow-embankment and overturned coming to rest on its roof.  V1 was
towed due to damage.  The driver was transported to a medical facility due to
injuries.  It was cloudy, the road was dry, and it was daylight at the time of
the crash.  No air bags deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a slight
right curve.  A deer ran into the roadway from the right side of the road.  V1
went off the left side of the road.  The front of V1 struck a 29 cm diameter
utility pole and came to rest off the left side of the road.  V1 was towed due
to damage.  The driver was transported to a medical facility due to injuries. It
was raining, the road was wet, it was dark and the road was lighted at the time
of the crash.  Both frontal air bags deployed.
V1 was traveling north when it departed the roadway on the right side and
impacted a guardrail.  V1 then rolled over on its right side one-quarter turn
before coming to final rest.  V1 was towed due to disabling damage.  The
occupant was transported to an area hospital via ambulance.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two lane two way rural roadway, and lost
control due to ice and snow.  Vehicle #1 started to rotate clockwise departed
roadway and impacted the south guardrail with the front of the vehicle.  Vehicle
#1 was towed due to disabling vehicle damage.  No injuries to report.
Vehicle's air bags did not deploy.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road.  V2 traveling north
on the same undivided two-lane road ahead of V1.  V2 stopped for a bus in the
roadway. The back of V2 was contacted by the front of V1.  V2 was towed due to
damage.  The driver of V2 was transported due to injuries. The weather was
clear, the road was dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.   No air
bags deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane road approaching and
intersection controlled by a stop sign.  V2 was traveling north on the
intersecting undivided two-lane road approaching the same intersection as V1.
The driver of V1 attempted to make a right turn at the intersection.  The right
side of V2 was struck by the front of V1.  V2 came to rest off the left side of
the road.  V1 came to rest in the intersection.  V2 was towed due to damage.  No
occupants of either vehicle were transported due to injuries.  It was raining,
the road was wet, it was dark and the road was not lighted at the time of the
crash.  No air bags in either vehicle deployed.
Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #3 stopped at traffic light while traveling east.
Vehicle #2 was traveling east and impacted the back of Vehicle #1 with the front
of Vehicle #2.  Vehicle #1 then impacted the back of Vehicle #3 with the front
of Vehicle #1.  Vehicle #2 frontal air bags deployed.  Vehicles #1 and 2 were
towed due to disabling vehicle damage.  Vehicle #3 was a non-tow.  No injuries
to report.
Vehicle #1 was traveling westbound departed the roadway on the right side
impacting a 10cm tree with its right front.  Vehicle #1 then entered back onto
the roadway traveling west crossing over the roadway and departing the roadway
on the left side impacting a snow bank causing the vehicle to rollover onto its
right side then continued to rollover for 60 meters and coming to final rest on
it's roof on the eastbound shoulder.  Driver of vehicle not injured.  Occupant
#2 was fully ejected from the vehicle and was transported to area hospital.
Vehicle #1 was towed and destroyed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve and approaching an intersecting roadway to the right.  Vehicle 2 was
traveling south on the intersecting roadway negotiating a right curve on a
downgrade.  The intersection was controlled by a stop sign for V2.  The driver
of V2 attempted to make a left turn at the intersection.  As both vehicles
crossed paths the left side of V2 was contacted by the front of V1.  Both
vehicles rotated counter-clockwise.  V1 came to rest facing east in the roadway.
V2 continued to rotate and went off the south side of the roadway.  The front
of V2 struck a shallow drainage ditch and the vehicle came to rest off the
roadway facing westward.
V1 was making a left turn at a three-way intersection, in order to travel north,
and struck the east side curb with its right front wheel. During this initial
impact V1 left the roadway and struck a large rock with its undercarriage and
rolled over two-quarter turns. V1 came to final rest on the roadway, in its
original travel, lane facing northbound.
While V1 was traveling northbound it crossed left of center and rotated
clockwise as it entered on-coming traffic. During this occurrence V2 and V3 were
traveling southbound on the same roadway directly in front of V1. As V1 and V2
crossed paths the right side-plane of V2 contacted the front end-plane of V2.
During this initial impact V3 veered to the left and crossed left of center. V2
began to rotate clockwise after initial contact and also traveled left of
center. As V2 and V3 crossed paths the front end-plane of V2 contacted the right
side-plane of V3. V1 rotated clockwise after initial contact with V2 and
departed the roadway on the west side of travel where V1 traveled up an
embankment, backwards, until arriving a final rest.
Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a
sharp left curve on a downgrade slope.  V1 went off the right side of the road.
The right front wheel struck a large rock.  The vehicle continued and came back
across the roadway.  V1 then went off the left side of the road and the front
of the vehicle struck a drainage ditch.  V1 came to rest off the left side of
the road.  V1 was towed due to disabling damage.  The driver was transported to
a medical facility via ambulance.  It was snowing, the road was snow/ice covered
and it was daylight at the time of the crash. The frontal air bags and the
driver knee bag deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve on an upgrade.  V1 went off the right side of the road.  The vehicle
rotated counterclockwise and the right side of the vehicle swiped a 70 cm
diameter tree.  V1 came back across the roadway and went off the left side of
the road where the vehicle came to rest. V1 was towed due to damage.  No
occupants of the vehicle were transported due to injuries. The weather was
clear, the road was slush covered and it was dawn at the time of the crash. The
frontal air bags deployed.
As V1 was traveling northbound, while negotiating a left curve, it started to
rotate counter clockwise.  V1 departed the east side of the roadway and
contacted a metal guardrail. This impact caused V1 to rollover towards the
roadway. V1 came to final rest on its roof in the original travel lane. V1 was
towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east crossed over the left lane line into the westbound
lane, departed the roadway and impacted the north guardrail with the front of
the vehicle.  Vehicle #1 then rotated counter clockwise and impacted the north
guardrail with the right side of the vehicle.  Vehicle #1's air bags did not
deploy.  Occupant of vehicle transported to area hospital.  Vehicle #1 was towed
due to disabling vehicle damage.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a five-lane undivided roadway in the second
lane from the right.  Vehicle 2 was traveling south on the same undivided
five-lane roadway in the right lane. V2 approached some vehicles, which were
decelerating in that lane.  V2 changed lanes to the right lane as the traffic in
that lane also started to decelerate.  The back of V2 was impacted by the front
of V1.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.  V1 was towed due to damage.
No occupants of either vehicle were transported. No air bags deployed in V1.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a left
curve.  V1 went off the right side of the road.  The front of the vehicle struck
a post and wire type guardrail. V1 started to rotate clockwise.  The left side
of the vehicle struck another post and cable type guardrail and the vehicle
mounted the guardrail.  The vehicle continued to travel along the guardrail in a
westerly direction.  The left side of the vehicle struck a 4 cm wide wooden
signpost. The vehicle continued to travel westerly and overturned.  The vehicle
came to rest at the bottom of a ditch-line facing east on its roof.  The driver
was ejected.  V1 was towed due to disabling damage.  The driver of V1 expired at
the scene.  The weather was clear, the road was dry, it was dark and the road
was lighted at the time of this crash.
Vehicle #1 was headed north, stopped in the roadway to make a left turn.
Vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same roadway and impacted the rear of
Vehicle #1.  Vehicle #3 was traveling south on the same roadway when Vehicle #1
crossed over the double yellow line and impacted the front of Vehicle #3 with
the front. The 3 vehicles were towed due to disabling vehicle damage.  No air
bags deployed in any of the vehicles.  Vehicle #1 occupant #1 was transported to
the hospital.
Vehicle 1 was traveling westbound on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a
left curve. Due to icy roadway conditions V1 left the north side of the road.
The front of V1 struck an 8 cm wide signpost, which fell and shattered V1's
windshield. V1 continued forward until its front/undercarriage struck the ground
on the far side of a shallow ditch line. V1 was towed due to disabling damage.
The weather was sleet/hail, the road was snow/ice covered and it was daylight at
the time of the crash.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road negotiating a slight
left curve.  V1 went off the right side of the road.  The front of V1 struck a
mailbox post.  V1 continued off the right side of the road.  V1 rotated
clockwise and the right side of the vehicle struck a 60 cm diameter tree.  The
vehicle continued to rotate and came to rest off the right side of the road
facing west.  V1 was towed due to damage.  The two rear seat passengers were
transported due to injuries.  The weather was clear, the road was dry, it was
dark and the road was not lighted at the time of the crash.  The driver's
frontal air bag deployed.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east, when a deer entered the roadway from the north
shoulder.  Vehicle #1 applied the brakes without lockup but impacted the deer
with the front of the vehicle.  Vehicle #1 was towed due to disabling vehicle
damage.  Occupant of vehicle not injuried.  Frontal air bags did not deploy.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north V1 departed the roadway to the right and impacted
one 10cm tree with the front, continued north and impacted a 45cm tree with the
front right of the vehicle.  Vehicle 1 then continued and impacted a 40cm tree
with the front left of the vehicle.  Vehicle 1 was towed due to disabling
vehicle damage.  Occupant was transported to a hospital for treatment.
Vehicle #2 was traveling south on an undivided two-way, two-lane roadway.
Vehicle #2 was stopped to make a left turn into a driveway.  Vehicle #1
traveling south on the same roadway impacted vehicle #2 in the rear with the
front of Vehicle #1.  Drivers of both vehicles transported to area hospitals.
Vehicle #1 towed due to disabling damage.  Vehicle #2 was a non-tow.
Vehicle 1 (V2 on PAR) was traveling south on an undivided two-lane road.  V2 (V1
on PAR), a tractor-trailer, was also traveling south on the same undivided
two-lane road to the rear of V1.  A deer ran into the roadway in front of V1.
The driver of V1 applied the brakes.  The back of V1 was struck by the front of
V2.  V1 came to rest partially off the left side of the road.  V2 came to rest
off the right side of the road.  V1 was towed due to damage.  The three
occupants of V1 were transported to a medical facility due to injuries.  The
weather was clear, the road was dry, it was dark and the road was not lighted at
the time of the crash.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a divided two-lane road.  V1 went off the right
side of the road.  The right side of V1 swiped a guardrail and a curb, (one
event).  The vehicle crossed the roadway and went off the left side of the road.
The front of V1 struck a guardrail and the vehicle came to rest partially in
the roadway.  V1 was towed due to damage.  No occupants of the vehicle were
transported due to injuries. It was snowing, the road was snow/ice covered and
it was daylight at the time of the crash.  No air bags deployed.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on an undivided two-lane road.  Vehicle 2 was
traveling south on the same undivided two-lane road. V1 crossed into the
southbound lane. The front of V1 struck the front of V2.  V2 pushed V1
southbound slightly after impact.  Both vehicles came to rest in the roadway.
Both vehicles were towed due to damage.  The driver of V1 was transported to a
trauma center where he expired.  The two rear seat passengers in V2 who were
seated in child safety seats were transported due to injuries.  The driver of V2
sought treatment later.  The weather was clear, the road was dry and it was
daylight at the time of the crash.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-way, two-lane roadway approaching a
three-way intersection. V2 was traveling westbound approaching the same
intersection. As both vehicles crossed paths, the front end-plane of V1
contacted the front end-plane of V2.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east on an undivided two-lane, two-way roadway.
Vehicle #1 was negotiating a right curve in the roadway, departed the roadway on
the north side.  Then started to rotate clockwise and impacted with a large
stonewall with the front of the vehicle.  Vehicle #1 continued and impacted a
mailbox with the front right side of the vehicle.  Vehicle #1 continued up an
earth embankment and rolled over.  Vehicle #1 then landed on its roof in a large
85cm tree and impacted a support cable with the left side of the vehicle.
Vehicle #1 was towed due to disabling vehicle damage.  Frontal air bags did not
deploy.  There were a total of 7 occupants in the vehicle at the time of the
crash.  Four of the occupants were transported to area hospitals for treatment.
V1 was traveling southbound on an undivided two-lane road, negotiating a left
curve. V1 went off the left side of the roadway until the front of V1 struck a
guardrail. V1 returned to the roadway, crossed both lanes of traffic and went
off the right side of the roadway until the front of V1 struck an embankment. V1
rolled over, left side leading, back into the roadway and came to rest on its
wheels. V1 continued to travel southbound until departing the left side of the
roadway where the front of V1 contacted a utility pole. V1 came to final rest
against this pole.
V1, V2, V4 and V5 were traveling north on a two lane undivided roadway.  V3 was
traveling south on the same roadway.  V1 and V2 were stopped in traffic, V4
slowing for V1 and V2.  V5 struck V4 in the rear with its front.  V4 was pushed
forward and struck V2 in the rear with its front.  V2 was pushed forward and
struck V1 in the rear with its front.  V5 steered left, crossed the center line
into the southbound lane and struck V3 in the left side with its front.  V3 came
to rest facing south off the west side of the roadway.  V5 came to rest facing
in a northwesterly direction in the roadway.  V1, V2 and V4 came to rest facing
north in the roadway.  V3, V4 and V5 were towed due to damage.  Driver's airbag
deployed in V3.  Occupants of V3, V4 and V5 were transported to hospital for
injuries.
Vehicle 1 was traveling east on an undivided three-lane road negotiating a left
turn and approaching an intersection controlled by a traffic signal.  V2 was
traveling west from a driveway and approaching the same intersection as V1,
which was also controlled by a traffic signal for V2.  V2 started to cross the
intersection as V1 made a left turn into the intersection.  The left side of V2
was struck by the front of V1.  Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.
V1 was towed due to damage.  V2 was driven from the scene with steering damage.
No occupants of either vehicle were transported due to injuries.  The weather
was clear, the road was dry and it was daylight at the time of the crash.  The
frontal air bags in V1 deployed.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane, two-way undivided roadway.
Vehicle #2 was traveling north on the same roadway.  Vehicle #1 crossed over the
double lane line and impacted Vehicle #2 on the left front corner with the
front of Vehicle #1.  Vehicle #1 rotated counterclockwise back across the
southbound lane and came to final rest facing in a northwesterly direction.
Vehicle #2 after impact continued into the southbound lane and came to final
rest in a northwesterly direction.   Occupants of both vehicles were transported
to area hospitals.  Both vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.  The
driver's air bag in vehicle #1 deployed due to impact forces.
V1 was traveling southbound on an undivided two-way, two-lane roadway
negotiating a left curve when V1 departed the roadway on the west side of the

This remote investigation focused on the crash dynamics and the non-deployment
of the frontal air bags in a 2004 Honda Civic.  The Honda was equipped with a
redesigned frontal air bag system and retractor mounted safety belt
pretensioners.  The vehicle was occupied by a 17-year-old female driver and a
17-year-old female front right passenger.  Both occupants were restrained at the
time of the crash by the vehicle's three-point lap and shoulder belt systems.
The crash occurred when the Honda departed the left side of the road and the
front and right side of the Honda's impacted six small diameter trees and a
large diameter tree.  This impact sequence did not deploy the frontal air bag
system; however, it did result in the actuation of the safety belt
pretensioners.  The driver sustained police reported incapacitating injuries and
was transported to a hospital where she was admitted for treatment.  The front
right passenger suffered police reported minor injuries.  She was transported to
a trauma center where treatment was administered.  However, its unknown if she
treated and released or hospitalized.  Both the driver and passenger were
transported to medical facilities that are non-cooperating with the NASS
program.  Therefore, the medical records were not obtained for this
investigation.

This crash occurred on a 4-lane roadway, not physically divided, with two
directions of travel.  Vehicle one (V1) was traveling eastbound intending to
continue his straight travel.  V1 went off the road to the left side.  While
traveling off the roadway, the vehicle had at least four events before final
rest.  The left front of the car struck the building, then the left rear struck
the building.  Then the car went up a handicap ramp and as it went off the
corner of the ramp the metal structure in the engine compartment, bounced up and
shorted out wires when it struck the hood, starting a fire.  After the car went
off the ramp, the car struck a concrete pole with the right front of the
vehicle.  The vehicle's final rest was back in the middle of the eastbound road
lanes, engulfed in flames.  The crash occurred on a wet, raining eve, in the
dark with street lights present.  The grade for V1 was downhill, -5% for the
precrash and -7% for the final rest.  The posted speed limit for V1 was 25 mph
(40kmp).  The driver of V1 left the scene, but returned while the police were
still present. V1 needed to be towed from the scene.

traffic signal.  Vehicle #1's front impacted the left side of Vehicle #2.
Vehicle #2 was towed from the scene.
Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two-lane roadway during daylight and dry
conditions.  Vehicle #1 is a right hand drive vehicle.  Vehicle #1 went off of
the roadway on the right side traveled through a grass lawn.  The vehicle's
front then went over a stone wall that is level at the approach striking a 110
cm in circumference tree with it's front.  The vehicle came to rest facing west
with its front wheels below the stone wall and it's back wheels on the stone
wall.  The driver was under the back of the at rest vehicle.  The vehicle was
towed from the scene of the event.
While attempting to changes lanes on a westbound interstate V1 lost traction and
struck the center barrier wall head-on. The vehicle entered a counter-clockwise
yaw, and overturned right side leading, before coming to final rest facing
northeast in the westbound lanes of traffic. This vehicle was towed due to
disabling damage.
V1 was southbound on a two lane rural road under dry/daylight conditions.   V1
steered right to avoid a dog in the road and impacted a utility pole with the
front.   V1 came to rest facing south off the right side of the road.   Belted
driver was transported for treatment.
V1 was traveling east on a straight two-lane roadway in dark and dry conditions
lighted by streetlights. The vehicle departed the left side of the roadway and
struck a tree with its front.     The non-belted driver was hospitalized.
The vehicle was towed due to disabling damage.
V1 was southbound on a two lane rural roadway under dry dark conditions.   V1
departed the left side of the road, travelled down an embankment, impacted a
utility pole with the left side, and rolled over onto its top.   V1 came to rest
on its top approximately 10 meters below the road surface.   Driver was
transported for treatment.   V1 was towed from the scene.
V1 was backing from a private drive onto a two lane urban road.   V2 was
eastbound on the road.   V1 back impacted V2 right side.   No injuries were
reported.   V1 was not towed, V2 was towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-way two-lane roadway that curves to the left
during daylight and dry conditions.  After V1 traveled through the left curve
it lost traction and began to rotate counter-clockwise. V1 departed the roadway
on the south side of travel and struck a raised portion of the ground with its
undercarriage. V1 then entered a ditch with its right side leading and struck
the far side ditch line where it came to final rest. It was reported that the
driver was partially ejected during this crash sequence.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a three lane eastbound side of an interstate
roadway in the emergency lane passing vehicles in the normal lanes.  Vehicle
went off  the roadway on the right side and struck a light pole with it's front,
then struck a guardrail with it's right side, then rolled over on it's top.
The driver was ejected.  The driver's was transported to a medical facility.
The vehicle was towed from the scene of the event.
V1 was traveling east, crossing a five-lane roadway when the right side was
contacted by the front of V2. Both vehicles traveled northwest of the
intersection after impact, and came to rest on the curb of the northbound lanes.
Both vehicles were towed from the crash due to disabling damage.
V1 departed the left side of an eastbound interstate, and traveled through a
grass median. As the driver corrected, the vehicle re-entered the eastbound
lanes and struck the guardrail at the right shoulder. V1 then re-entered the
eastbound lanes, where its front struck the back of V2. V2 entered a
counter-clockwise yaw, and struck the center concrete barrier wall head-on. V2
then traveled southeast across the eastbound lanes where it struck the guardrail
on the right shoulder of the eastbound lanes with its front. V1 after impact to
V2's back, traveled northeast, striking the center barrier wall head-on where
it came to rest.    Both vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.
V1 was northbound on a four lane highway curved to the right.   V1 departed the
road to the left, impacted a rock wall with the front, and rolled over onto the
top.  The driver was hospitalized, and V1 was towed from the scene.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane rural road under dark/dry conditions.   V1
departed the road to the right and impacted two wooden mailbox posts with the
front.   V1 continued east and impacted a wooden utility pole with the front.
V1 rotated clockwise and impacted a steel guardrail with the left side.   The
belted driver was transported for treatment.   V1 was towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling north on a two-lane rural road when the vehicle departed the
right side of the roadway. As the driver attempted to correct, the vehicle
entered a clockwise yaw, traveled up an embankment and overturned to its left.
The vehicle came to rest on the roadway on its roof facing southeast.     The
occupants exited under their own power, and the vehicle was towed due to
disabling damage.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway during daylight and dry
conditions.  Vehicle #1 was towing a "fifth wheel" empty flat bed trailer.
Vehicle #2 was traveling east on a two lane roadway turning right at an
intersecting roadway.  Vehicle #2's front struck the right side of Vehicle #1,
Vehicle #2 then struck the right side of the trailer being towed by Vehicle #1.
Vehicle #2 was towed from the scene of the event.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a four lane roadway during dark/lighted and
dry conditions.  Vehicle went off of the roadway on the right side striking a
curb with it's right front tire then struck a railroad sign post with it's
front.  The driver was transported to a medical facility and the vehicle was
towed from the scene of the event.
V1 traveling north and V2 southbound collided head-on while negotiating a curve
of a three-lane urban roadway. After this initial impact both vehicles rotated
counter-clockwise to final rest. Both vehicles were towed due to disabling
damage.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east in the second travel lane of a five lane one-way
roadway during daylight and dry conditions.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south in
the inside travel lane of a four lane intersecting roadway.  Vehicle #1 traveled
into the intersection and contacted the right side of Vehicle #2 with it's
front.  The driver in Vehicle #2 was transported to a medical facility.  Both
vehicles were towed from the scene of the event.
V1 and V2 were both northbound on a two lane divided road.   V2 slowed for
traffic and the front of V1 impacted  the rear of V2.   V1 was towed from the
scene, V2 was not towed.
V1 and V2 were southbound on a five lane road.   V3 was westbound on an
intersecting two lane road.   The intersection is controlled by a traffic light.
As V3 passed through the intersection, V2 front impacted V3 right.   V3 spun
off the right side of the road, impacting a raised curb with the left front
tire, and then impacted the ground with the left side.   V2 spun clockwise and
the front of V1 impacted the right side of V2.      All three vehicles were
towed from the scene.
V1 traveling south on a two-lane asphalt rural road in dark and dry conditions

trees before coming to rest facing southwest at the second struck tree.     The
vehicle was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle #1 was traveling eastbound in the center lane of a six lane interstate
highway that has a center concrete divider wall. Vehicle #2 was traveling behind
Vehicle #1 on the same roadway. Vehicle #3, an unidentified medium/heavy truck,
was traveling westbound on the same roadway. Vehicle #3 lost a wheel and tire
that went over the concrete divider wall striking Vehicle #1 in the windshield
and roof and then striking Vehicle #2 in the hood, windshield and roof.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane rural road when it departed the roadway on the
south side of travel and struck a mailbox post with its front end-plane. V1
continued forward in a southeasterly direction until V1 struck a tree trunk with
its front end-plane. V1 came to final rest in the immediate vicinity of this
post secondary impact.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two-lane rural roadway in daylight and dry
conditions. V1 stopped for oncoming traffic before turning left at an
intersection when it was contacted from behind by V2. Both vehicles came to rest
in the westbound lane near the point of impact.     V1 was driven from the
crash, while V2 was towed due to disabling damage.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-lane rural trafficway when it departed the
roadway and struck a steel guardrail on the south side of the street with its
front end-plane. While off the roadway V1's front end-plane contacted a
signpost. V1 then tripped over, left side leading and rolled over two
quarter-turns.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway during daylight and dry
conditions.  Vehicle went off of the roadway on the right side and sideswiped
two mailboxes; then struck two mailboxes, a realty sign, and another mailbox
with it's front; then struck a utility cover with it's right front wheel, then
struck a utility pole with it's front.  The vehicle then had an engine fire.
The driver was transported to a medical facility.  The vehicle was towed from
the scene of the event.
V1 was eastbound on a two lane rural roadway.   As V1 exited a right curve, it
departed the road to the right entered into a field and impacted a barbed wire

ejected via the left front door.   V1 was towed from the scene.   V1 separated
at the left b-pillar, and was almost sheared in two.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway during daylight and dry
conditions.  Vehicle #1 completed a turn to the left then went off of the
roadway on the right side sideswiping two mailboxes. Vehicle #1 then crossed the
eastbound and westbound lanes going off of the roadway on the left side
striking a utility pole with it's front.  The vehicle then traveling backwards
after striking the pole coming to rest with it's front in the eastbound lane and
it's rear off of the roadway on the south side of the roadway.  The vehicle was
towed from the scene of the event.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a five-lane roadway that intersects with a
five-lane roadway that runs north and south.  The intersection is controlled by

curb of the northbound lane with it's front wheels, then struck an embankment

towed from the scene of the event.
V1 departed the right side of a two lane rural roadway in daylight and dry

V1 was westbound on a two lane road.   V1 departed the road to the right, and as

side of the road and impacted an embankment with the front.  V1 then impacted a
mailbox with the right side.   V1 rolled over, two-quarter turns and came to
rest on its roof within the roadway.
V1 was northbound on a four lane road under dry/dark conditions.   V2 was
westbound, pulling out of a parking lot, turning left when the front of V1
contacted the left side of V2.   Both vehicles were towed from the scene.
V1 departed the right side of the roadway, struck a culvert and overturned right
side leading. The vehicle completed three-quarter-turns coming to rest on the
driver side after striking a parked vehicle. D1 was transported to a medical
facility.    The vehicle was towed due to disabling damage.
V1 was westbound in an s-curve under dry/daylight conditions.   V2 was
eastbound.   V1 crossed over the centerline and sideswiped V2.   V1 departed the

Vehicle #1 was traveling east from an apartment driveway turning left.  Vehicle

Vehicle #1's left side was contacted by the front of Vehicle #2.  Both vehicles
were towed from the scene of the event.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane urban roadway when it began a clockwise
yaw while negotiating a right curve. V1 departed the right side of the roadway,
struck an embankment and overturned with its left side leading. V1 arrived at
final rest facing southwest near the center of the roadway after completing two
quarter-turns.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a two lane roadway that curves to the left.
Vehicle #1 rotated counterclockwise in the curve; overcorrected, then rotated
clockwise and traveled off of the right side of the roadway and struck a
guardrail with it's front. V1 then struck a utility pole with it's left side.
V1 traveling west was attempting to turn left from a two-way center turn lane of
a five-lane urban roadway in daylight and dry conditions. As V1 turned left,

to rest facing north near the center of the roadway. V2 traveled southeast

right at the intersection.      All three vehicles were towed due to disabling
damage.
V1 was traveling westbound while negotiating a left curve when it departed the
north side of the roadway and contacted a building with its front end-plane.
Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two lane roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling
east on an intersecting  roadway that has two eastbound lanes, a center grass
ditch median, a westbound left turn lane, and two westbound lanes.  Vehicle #2
was traveling in the inside eastbound travel lane.  Vehicle #3 was stopped in
the westbound left turn lane.  Vehicle #1 crossed the intersection to turn left
and was struck in the left side by the front of Vehicle #2, Vehicle #1 rotated
clockwise and Vehicle #2 rotated counterclockwise then the left side of Vehicle

Drivers of Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were transported to a medical facility.
Vehicle #1 and Vehicle #2 were towed from the event.  Vehicle #3 was not towed

V1 was westbound under daylight/rainy conditions.   V1 departed the road to the

V1 was traveling east on a two-lane urban road in dark, and dry conditions

Vehicle #1 was traveling north on a two-lane roadway that is controlled by a

roadway, the front of Vehicle #1 and the front of V2 contacted. The driver of
Vehicle #1 was transported to a medical facility.  Both vehicles were towed from
the scene.
V1 traveling east on a two-lane rural roadway departed the right side of the

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway that curves to the right.
Vehicle #1 went off of the roadway and struck a guardrail with it's front, then

V1 was northbound on a four lane divided urban roadway.   V2 was southbound in
the left turn lane.   As V2 turned left, the front of V1 impacted the right side

V1 was westbound in the center turn lane of a five lane road., V2 and V3 were

left, V2 front impacted V1 right side.   The two vehicles then sideslapped.   V1
front then impacted V3 front.    V1 came to rest facing northwest.   V2 crossed

facing east.
V1 and V2 were traveling west on a two-lane rural roadway in daylight and
raining conditions. V2 was slowing to turn left when the front of V1 contacted
the back of V2.     V2 was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle #1 was stopped in the outside on the three lane westbound side of an

V1 traveling south and V2 turning left to travel north at an intersection

V1 was northbound in the left turn lane of a five lane urban roadway.   V2 was
southbound.   As V1 turned left at the light, V2 front impacted V1 right side.
V1 fled the scene, and V2 was towed from the scene.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a five-lane interstate in daylight and dry
conditions. The driver was attempting to slow for traffic ahead. The vehicle

damage.
V1 was westbound on a four lane urban road.   V2, a heavy truck, was in front of
V1.   V1's front impacted V2's rear.   Driver of V1 was transported for
treatment.   V1 was towed from the scene, V2 was not.
V1 was  westbound on an interstate exit ramp.   V1 departed the road to the

clcokwise and impacted the embankment with its front and left sides.   V1 came
to final rest facing southwest off the right side of the ramp.   V1 was towed
from the scene.
V1 struck a bridge barrier wall with its front while in a clockwise yaw,

six-quarter turns as the vehicle traveled southeast across the roadway where its

disabling damage.
Vehicle #1 was headed east from a parking lot turn left onto a five lane roadway

travel lane of the five lane roadway (that has a center left/right turn lane).
Vehicle #2's front struck the left side of Vehicle #1.  Vehicle # 1 came to rest
facing northeast in the northbound lanes.  Vehicle #2 came to rest facing east

V1 was attempting to turn left into a fast food facility when the right side

V1 was westbound on a two lane road.   V1 departed the road to the right and

V1 was traveling eastbound on a two-way two-lane undivided roadway when it
tracked off the south side of the street and contacted a wooden fence and then
struck a wooden utility pole. V1 came to final rest in the immediate vicinity of
this pole impact.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a one lane entrance ramp that merges with the
two lane southbound side of a four lane roadway.  Vehicle #2 was traveling south

south in the outside travel lane.      Vehicle #1 was towed from the scene of
the event.  The driver of Vehicle #1 was transported to a medical facility.
Vehicle #2 was not towed, Vehicle #3 is a non-CDS vehicle.
V1 was southbound on a five lane road.   V2 was northbound.   V1 crossed over
into the north lanes and entered into a counterclockwise yaw.   The right side
of V1 impacted the front of V2.   Both vehicles were towed from the scene.
Vehicle #1 was traveling south on a curve to the left two lane roadway during
daylight and dry conditions.  Vehicle #1 entered the curve, began to rotate

struck a barn with the right front and then with the right rear.  Vehicle #1
came to rest facing north next to the barn.  The vehicle was towed from the
scene of the event.
V1 departed the left side of a two-lane rural roadway while negotiating a right

V1 was northbound on a two lane road.   V2 was eastbound on an intersecting
road.    V2 front impacted V1 left.   Both vehicles departed the road to the

Vehicle #1 was traveling west on a two lane roadway during daylight and dry
conditions approaching a four way stop controlled intersection.  Vehicle #2 was
traveling north on a two lane roadway approaching the same intersection.
Vehicle #1's front struck the right side of Vehicle #2 as it passed through the
intersection.  Vehicle #2 veered to the left and struck a large utility pole

front.  Vehicle #1 came to rest facing north in the center of the intersection.
The passenger in Vehicle #1 and the driver in Vehicle #2 were transported to a
medical facility.  Both vehicles were towed from the scene of the event.
The driver of V1 swerved right to avoid a ladder in the roadway. The vehicle
entered the right shoulder and the driver attempted to steer back left to

V1, V2, and V3 were all southbound on a two lane interstate in the outside lane.
A non contact vehicle slowed in front of V3.   V3 slowed and V1 front

scene.   V1 and V3 were not towed.
V1 traveling southeast in dark and dry conditions with no available streetlights
in the area departed the right of the roadway where the front impacted a
90-centimeter diameter concrete bridge support. The vehicle rotated clockwise

was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway that curves to the left

side and struck a mailbox that was anchored to a pole that was not struck, then

The driver was transported to a medical facility and the vehicle was towed
from the scene of the event.
V1 was northbound an a divided two lane road.   V1 departed the right side of
the road and impacted a large shrub with the front/undercarriage as it went down

Vehicle #1 was traveling east on a two lane roadway.  Vehicle was turning right

V1 was northbound on a three lane rural road under dry/dark conditions.   V2 was
eastbound on a two lane road.   The intersection is controlled by a stop sign

V1 departed the right side of an eastbound four-lane interstate in daylight and

Vehicle #1 was traveling north in the outside travel lane of a three lane

V1 was traveling south when it departed the right side of a two-lane roadway in

V1 was westbound on a two lane road.   V1 made a right turn onto an intersecting
road and impacted a legally parked vehicle on the north side.   V1 was towed

V1 and V3 were traveling south on a two-lane roadway negotiating a left curve in

V1 was traveling northbound on a two-way two-lane, undivided roadway approaching
a four-way intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound in lane one of a two-way
