V1 was traveling southbound in the second lane of a two-lane highway.  V1
drifted off the left roadside, the corrected right and lost traction.  V1
departed the road to the right, rotating clockwise.  On the right roadside, V1
traversed a ditch and its front impacted the opposite side.  V1 rotated
clockwise from impact and came to rest in the ditch.
V1 was traveling in the center lane of the three westbound lanes on a divided
six-lane road.  The crash occurred during a rain shower after V1 began to
hydroplane and departed the right roadside while rotating clockwise.  V1
contacted a guardrail with its front plane and continued through the guardrail.
V1 contacted the guardrail a second time with its left plane.  V1 continued and
contacted some small trees with its front plane.  V1 came to rest on the
roadside.  It appears that the section of the guardrail had been damaged prior
to this crash and a patch section had been placed between the damaged areas.
This may have contributed to the rail penetrating the occupant compartment.
V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags, dual front side air bags and dual
first and second row side curtains.  All of the left side air bags deployed in
V1.  V1 was towed from the crash scene due to disabling damage.    The
unrestrained driver of V1 was ejected from the vehicle during the crash.  He was
transported to a local hospital and released from the facility's emergency
room.
V1 was traveling east on a two-way, two-lane road when it departed the right
roadside and contacted two trees with its front.  V1 came to rest on the
roadside after impact.
V1 was traveling southbound and approaching a sharp curve left.  V1 lost
traction negotiating the curve and departed the road over the right edge, where
its front impacted a steep dirt embankment.
V1 was traveling west in lane two of the westbound lanes of a divided interstate
road approaching an entrance junction.  There was a non-contact vehicle in lane
one of the westbound lanes that attempted to move left into lane two.  The
driver of V1 steered left and departed its travel lane into the median.  The
driver of V1 then attempted to maneuver her vehicle back into her lane.  This
maneuver caused her to lose control of her vehicle.  V1 crossed over all lanes
including the entrance lane while rotating clockwise.  V1 departed the roadway
and went down an embankment.  V1 contacted two small bushes with its left side
and then rolled over with its left side leading.  While rolling, V1 contacted
two trees with its top and then another tree with its right side.  V1 came to
rest on its left side after rolling 5-quarter turns.    V1 was towed from the
crash scene due to disabling damage.  The restrained driver of V1 sustained
injury and was transported to a local hospital for treatment.
V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane highway.  V1 departed the road to the
right side, where V1 contacted trees on both the left and right sides in a
sideswipe motion, then impacted a tree with its front plane, shearing the tree.
The tree fell on the roof of V1 as it came to rest.
V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane highway.  V1 departed the road to the
left side, where its front impacted a guardrail.  V1 rode up the guardrail and
rolled towards its right side, completing two quarter-turns and coming to rest
on its top in the roadway.
V1 was traveling southbound in lane one of the three southbound lanes of a
divided road.  As V1 approached the crossover area of the divider, a non-contact
vehicle pulled out of the crossover area.  The driver of V1 steered left and
braked and V1 departed the roadway to the left into the median, entered a
counterclockwise rotation, traveled through the median across another crossover
section and into the continuation of the median, then tripped over and  rolled
left 10 quarter turns before coming to rest in the median on its top.    V1 was
towed from the crash scene due to disabling damage.
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane, two-way road while negotiating a curve on
a wet roadway.  V1 entered the curve and lost control.  V1 departed the roadway
to the right while rotating clockwise.  V1 went into a ditch causing its
undercarriage to contact the ditch.  The rear of V1 also contacted the ditch.
V1 then began to roll with its right side leading.  V1 rolled two-quarter turns
and came to rest on its top while still in the ditch.    V1 was not equipped
with air bags.  V1 was towed from the scene due to disabling damage.    The
restrained driver of V1 sustained injury and was transported to a local hospital
for treatment.  He was treated and released from the facility's emergency room.
V1 was traveling on a two-lane opposite direction roadway. V1 approached a curve
and ran off the roadway to the right. V1 stuck a small sign and then a culvert.
V1 began to rotate counterclockwise and crossed both lanes of the roadway and
departed the roadway to the left. As V1 departed the roadway to the left it
tripped and rolled right side leading and struck a wooden fence. V1 came to
final rest facing in a westerly direction.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal
air bags per the police report they did not deploy. V1 was reportedly towed from
the scene due to damage.
V1 was traveling west on a two-lane, double line divided roadway.  V1 exited the
roadway to the right, striking a small tree on its front right corner.  V1
continued westward contacting two small trees with its front.  V1 came to rest
upon those two trees.
V1 was traveling a two-lane, double line divided roadway that curved to the
left.  V1, in an attempt to avoid a deer in the roadway, exited the roadway to
the right.  V1 traveled up an embankment and contacted two small trees with its
frontal plane.  V1 came to rest facing east.
V1 was traveling west while negotiating a left curve.  V1 departed the roadway
to the right where it contacted a ditch with its front.  V1 came to rest in the
ditch.
V1 was traveling in lane two of a four lane interstate highway with the lanes
separated by a grass median area. V1 was towing a u-haul trailer and the trailer
started fish tailing and then jackknifed. This caused V1 to rotate
counterclockwise. V1 rolled with the right side leading and came to final rest
on its left side facing in a northwesterly direction.   V1 was towed from the
scene due to damage.
V1 was traveling in lane 1 of two southbound lanes.  V1 veered off the right
shoulder, overcorrected and began to rotate counterclockwise.  V1 struck a metal
guardrail in the median with its frontal plane.  V1 overturned, leading with
the right plane, and came to final rest in lane 2.  V1 was reportedly towed due
to disabling damage.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane opposite direction roadway. For
unknown reasons V1 lost control and departed the roadway, continued down an
embankment and contacted a tree with its front.
Vehicle one was traveling north on a two-way, two-lane road.  It was raining and
the roads were wet.  For an unknown reason, V1 lost control on the roadway and
departed the roadway to the left.  V1 contacted a fire hydrant with its right
side.  V1 continued to travel and contacted a fence with its right side.  There
were also several small trees along fence that was contacted by the right side
of V1.  V1 penetrated the fence and began to roll with its right side.  During
V1's roll its top plane contacted a large tree.  V1 came to rest on its top.
V1 was equipped with two air bags of which the driver's side deployed during the
crash.  V1 was towed due to disabling damage.    The unrestrained driver of V1
was fatally injured  and  died while on scene.
V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane roadway.  V1 drifted off the right
road edge, correct left and lost traction.  V1 rotated counter-clockwise as it
departed the road to the left side.  On the left roadside, the right side of V1
knocked down a signpost and a utility box.  V1 continued to rotate around, and
its left side struck a tree, bringing V1 to rest.  The driver was fatally
injured.
V1 was traveling southbound in lane two of a four-lane interstate highway with
the lanes separated by a grass median without positive barriers. V2 was
traveling in lane one of the northbound traffic lanes. Both directions were
level and straight and the crash occurred during daylight hours.     V1 veered
into the median and entered the northbound lanes. The right side of V1 contacted
the front of V2. After impact V1 rotated clockwise and came to final rest on
the right side of the northbound lanes facing in a southeasterly direction.
After impact V2 continued northbound and rotated slightly clockwise coming to
final rest in lane one of the northbound traffic lane facing in a northeasterly
direction.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags that per the police
report deployed. V2 was equipped with dual frontal air bags both of which
deployed during the crash. Both vehicles were towed from the scene due to
damage.
V1 was traveling north in lane two of the northbound lanes while approaching an
on ramp onto the northbound lanes.  As V1 neared the ramp, a noncontact vehicle
attempted to merge into the northbound traffic.  The driver of V1 steered left
in an attempt to avoid contact with the noncontact vehicle.  V1 departed the
roadway left into the median where it contacted a ditch with its front and then
rolled two-quarter turns with its right side leading.  V1 came to rest in the
median while on its top.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags that did
not deploy during the crash.  V1 was towed from the crash scene due to disabling
damage.    The restrained driver of V1 sustained injury and was transported to
a medical facility for treatment.
V1 was traveling south on a two lane, double line divided roadway.  V1 exited
the roadway to the right.  The frontal plane of V1 contacted the embankment and
then struck two smaill saplings.      V1 was towed due to disabling damage.  V1
was equipped with dual, frontal airbags, which did deploy.    The restrained
driver of V1 was transported to an area hospital.  It is unknow if she was
admitted or treated and released.
V1 was traveling on an interstate highway with six-lanes and a concrete barrier
separating the opposite directions. V1 was traveling northbound and for unknown
reasons traveled off the right side of the roadway. V1 continued down an
embankment and back up the other side and rolled with the right side leading at
least four quarter turns coming to final rest on its wheels.    V1 was equipped
with dual front air bags neither of which deployed. V1 was towed from the scene
due to damage.    The restrained driver of V1 was transported to a local
hospital and was admitted for three days for sustained injuries.
V1 was traveling on an interstate highway in lane three negotiating a curve to
the left when a truck encroached into her lane causing the driver of V1 to steer
left to avoid impact. The driver of V1 lost control and V1 began rotating
counterclockwise and departed the roadway to the left and the right side of V1
contacted the positive barrier in the median area.    V1 was equipped with dual
frontal air bags unknown if any deployment occurred. V1 was towed from the scene
due to damage.    The second row right passenger was transported to a local
hospital for sustained injuries unknown if he was admitted or treated and
released. No other occupant was injured.
V1 was traveling southbound and turning left into a private drive.  V2 was
traveling northbound and passing the private drive on its right.  As V1 turned,
the front of V2 impacted the right side of V1.  V1 rotated clockwise and struck
two mailboxes with its right side, where it came to rest.
V1 was traveling south in lane 2 of a four lane roadway in which two lanes are
separated by a median.  V2 was traveling the same roadway but was heading north
in lane 2.  V1 was attempting to make a left turn across the northbound lanes
into a private drive.  V2's frontal plane contacted the right plane of V1.    V1
was not towed.  V2 was towed due to disabling damage.  Both V1 and V2 were
equipped with dual, frontal airbags, of which only V2's deployed.  V2 was also
equipped with frontal driver knee airbags and dual side air bags. The driver
side knee air bag deployed.       The restrained drivers of both vehicles were
not injured.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane roadway, curving left.  V1 departed
the road to the right side and traversed a grass field.  V1 emerged from the
field on a, east-west crossing street, where V2 (a garbage truck) was stopped at
the stop sign.  The front of V1 impacted the left side of V2.
V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two-lane roadway.  A pile of
gravel was in the roadway.  V1 struck the pile of gravel, causing disabling
frontal damage.
V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane opposite direction roadway. V1 came up
on V3 who was stopped in traffic in the southbound lane. V1 was unable to stop
in time so V1 steered into the northbound lane. As V1 was in the northbound lane
the right side of V1 contacted the front of V2, which was traveling north in
the northbound lane. After contact with the right side of V1, V2 began to rotate
clockwise and the left rear of V2 contacted the right side of V3. After impact
V1 came to final rest partially in the northbound lane facing southbound. After
impact V2 came to final rest in the middle of the roadway facing in a
northeasterly direction. After impact V3 came to final rest facing southbound in
the southbound lane.    All three vehicles were towed from the scene due to
damage.
V1 was traveling on a four-lane roadway with the north and southbound lanes
separated by a grass median without positive barriers. V1 had a slight negative
grade. V2 was traveling the same roadway in the opposite direction and V2 had a
slight positive grade. The crash occurred during daylight hours.    V1 was
traveling in lane one of the southbound lanes when the left rear tire had a
tread separation causing the driver of V1 to loose control. V1 proceeded through
the median rotating counterclockwise and entered the northbound lanes rolling
with the right side leading. V2 was traveling in lane one of the northbound lane
and steered right in an attempt of missing V1. The undercarriage of V1 struck
the upper left side of V2 and rolled over V2. V1 continued and came to final
rest facing in a southerly direction on the right roadside on its wheels. V2
continued and came to final rest facing north bound on the right roadside. V2
had a small fire in the engine compartment.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal
air bags neither of which deployed during the accident. V2 was not equipped
with air bags. Both vehicles were towed from the scene due to damage.    The
restrained driver of V1 was extricated and flown to an area trauma center it is
unknown if he was admitted or was treated and released. The restrained driver of
V2 received fatal injuries in the crash.
V1 was attempting to crossover a busy roadway when its right side was contacted
by the front of V2 (an ambulance).  Both vehicles came to rest on the right
roadside.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags and two side air bags.
The right side airbag along with the two frontal air bags deployed during the
crash.  V2 was equipped with dual frontal air bags that did not deploy during
the crash.    The restrained driver of V1 was injured and transported from the
crash scene to a hospital where was admitted.  The restrained driver of V2
sustained injury and was transported to a local hospital and released.  The
restrained rear-facing occupant sustained injury and was transported to a local
hospital and released.  The right rear occupant was strapped down on a stretcher
and also sustained injury.  She was transported to a local hospital and
released
V1 was traveling a two-lane opposite direction roadway with lanes separated by a
double yellow line; V1 had a slight positive grade. V2 was traveling a two-lane
opposite direction roadway with the lanes separated by a dashed yellow line V2
had a level grade. The accident occurred during darkness.    V1 was approaching
a T intersection and had a stop sign. After stopping V1 proceeded to make a left
turn onto the intersecting roadway. V2 was approaching the same intersection
when the front of V2 struck the front of V1. After impact V1 rotated clockwise
and came to final rest facing in a northwesterly direction half on the roadway
and half off the roadway. After impact V2 rotated counterclockwise and came to
an uncontrolled stop off the roadway to the left facing in a northwesterly
direction.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags neither of which
deployed during the crash. V2 was not equipped with air bags. Both vehicles were
towed due to damage.    The restrained driver of V1 was transported to a local
hospital where he was admitted for 5 days for sustained injuries. The restrained
driver of V2 was transported to a local hospital for sustained injuries unknown
if she was admitted or treated and released.
V1 was traveling a two-lane opposite direction roadway with the lanes separated
by double solid yellow lines. V1 was traveling northbound in a rain shower and
departed the roadway to the right. V1 overcorrected to the left and V1 began to
rotate counterclockwise. V1 crossed over the north and southbound lanes and
departed the roadway to the left, then impacted a mailbox and a tree with the
right plane before coming to final rest against the tree.     V1 was towed from
the scene due to damage
V1 was traveling south on a two-lane road while negotiating a right curve.  A
deer jumped into the roadway from the right causing the driver to steer right in
an attempt to avoid a collision with the animal.  V1 departed the roadway to
the right where it contacted a bridge rail with its front.  V1 rotated clockwise
along the bridge rail with its front..     The PAR reports driver's frontal air
bag deployment as a result of the crash.  V1 was towed from the crash scene due
to disabling damage.    The restrained driver of V1 sustained injury and was
transported from the scene to a local emergency room.
V1 was traveling southbound in a two-lane roadway, approaching a T-intersection.
V1 traversed the intersection and departed the road on the opposite side.  The
front of V1 impacted a guardrail, riding up and over the guardrail.  V1
continued forward and struck a house, bringing V1 to rest.
V2, V3, and V4 were stopped in the right lane of a two-lane roadway awaiting the
traffic light to change. V1 was approaching the stopped vehicles. V1 was
traveling in the right lane and for unknown reasons was unable to stop with the
front of V1 impacting the rear of V2 causing the front of V2 to impact the rear
of V3 causing the front of V3 to impact the rear of V4. The roadway had an up
hill grade to it and the crash occurred during daylight hours.    V2 and V3 were
towed from the scene due to damage. V1 and V4 were not towed from the scene.
The restrained driver of V2 was transported to a local hospital for sustained
injuries. No one else was injured in the crash.
V1 was traveling eastbound and approaching an intersection to turn right.  V2
was traveling southbound and approaching the same intersection.  As V1 turned,
the front of V2 impacted the left side of V1.
V1 was traveling north in a lane controlled by a stop sign and approaching a
four-legged intersection.  V2 was traveling west on the intersecting road and
attempting to pass through the intersection.  V1 attempted to crossover the
intersecting road and its right side was contacted by the front of V2.  Both
vehicles rotated causing the right side of V1 to contact the left side of V2.
Both vehicle continued northwest and came to rest on the northwest roadside.
V1 was towed and disabled.  V2 was towed, however, it did not sustain disabling
damage.
V1 was negotiating a left curve while traveling west when the vehicle rolled
over with its left side leading.  V1 rolled one complete turn and came to rest
on the roadside, facing east.      V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags
that did not deploy.  V1 was towed from the crash scene due to disabling damage.
The restrained occupants of V1 sustained minor injuries and were transported
to a local hospital for treatment
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane road, curving right.  V1 lost traction
around the curve and rotated clockwise as it departed the road to the right
side.  On the roadside, the left side of V1 contacted a mailbox.  V1 continued
off-road and struck a tree with its front, bringing V1 to rest.
V1 was traveling east in the left turn lane attempting to turn left on a
four-way controlled intersection.  V2 was traveling in lane two of the westbound
lanes attempting to pass through the intersection heading west.  As both
vehicles entered the intersection, the front of V2 contacted the right side of
V1.  Both vehicles came to rest in the intersection.    V1 was equipped with
dual frontal air bags that did not deploy.  V2 was also equipped with dual
frontal air bags.  The driver's air bag in V2 was reported as deployed.  Both
vehicles were towed from the crash scene due to disabling damage.    The
restrained driver of V1 and V2 did not sustain injury.
V1 was traveling north on a two-lane opposite direction roadway with a left turn
lane approaching a four-legged intersection. V2 was approaching the same
four-legged intersection heading west. The front of V1 impacted the left side of
V2. After impact V1 continued straight coming to final rest facing north. After
impact V2 rotated counterclockwise and came to rest facing in an easterly
direction.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags neither of which
deployed. V2 was equipped with dual frontal air bags neither of which deployed.
V2 was towed from the scene due to damage. V1 was not towed from the scene.
The restrained driver of V1 was not injured. The restrained driver and the
restrained front right passenger of V2 were not injured.
V1 was traveling a two-lane opposite direction roadway. V1 for unknown reasons
lost control while negotiating a turn to the right. V1 departed the roadway to
the left and then began rotating clockwise and translating across both lanes of
traffic and departed the roadside to the right. V1 continued off the roadside
and impacted a tree with its left side. V1 came to final rest against the tree.
V1 was towed from the scene due to damage.  The restrained driver of V1 was
fatally injured in the accident.
V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane roadway.  V2 was slowing ahead of V1.
V3 was stopped ahead of V2.  V3 was stopped ahead of V3.  The front of V1
impacted the back of V2.  V2 moved ahead and struck the back of V3.  V3 moved
ahead and struck the back of V4.
V1 was negotiating a left curve while traveling north on a wet roadway during a
rain shower.  The driver of V1 lost control of the vehicle sending V1 into a
counterclockwise rotation off the right roadside and down an embankment.  V1
impacted three trees with its rear.  V1 came to rest on the roadside facing
south.    V1 was towed due to disabling damage. The restrained driver of V1
sustained injury, was transported to a medical facility and admitted.
V1 was a tractor-trailer with a load of logs was stopped in the roadway
attempting a turn. V2 was traveling westbound approaching V1. It was dark and
the driver of V2 didn't see the cargo of logs in his lane until the last minute.
V2 turned to the right and tried to avoid the logs. V2 was unable to avoid the
logs and the load of logs on V1 contacted the windshield and roof area of V2.
V2 had dual frontal air bags neither of which deployed during the accident. V2
was towed from the scene due to damage.    The restrained driver of V2 was
transported to a local hospital where he was treated and released for sustained
injuries. The driver of V1 was not injured
V1, V2, and V3 were all traveling north on the same roadway in the number one
lane.  V3 was stopped intending to turn into a private drive and V2 was
decelerating intending to stop behind V3. The front of V1 impacted the rear of
V2. The impact propelled V2 forward and the front of V2 impacted the rear of V3.
V1 and V2 were traveling east in the far right left turn lane while approaching
an intersection.  V2 was decelerating and steering left to maneuver into the
inside lane.  V3 was stopped ahead of V1 and V2.  The front of V1 contacted the
right rear of V2.  V1 continued and contacted the rear of V3.  All vehicles came
to rest in the left turn lanes, facing east.    V1 was equipped with dual
frontal air bags that both deployed during the crash.  V2 was equipped with dual
frontal air bags that did not deploy.  V3 was equipped with dual frontal air
bags, along with side curtains.  No air bags deployed in V3.  V1 was towed due
to disabling damage.  Neither V2 nor V3 were towed from the crash scene.    The
restrained driver of V1 sustained injury and was transported to a medical
facility for treatment.  She was treated and released from the facility's
emergency room.  The right rear passenger of V1 who, was restrained in a CSS,
did not sustain injury.  The restrained drivers of V2 and V3 did not sustain
injury.
V1 was traveling southbound and about to turn left into a private lot.  The
driver of V1 lost consciousness, and V1 departed the road to the left, where its
front impacted a building.
V1 was traveling on an unmarked roadway during daylight hours and wet conditions
and for unknown reasons lost control and departed the roadway to the left. V1
made contact with a street sign with the front plane and began to rotate
clockwise and the left plane contacted a culvert causing V1 to roll and to come
to final rest on its top plane facing in a northerly direction.    V1 was
equipped with a driver's side air bag, which did not deploy during the accident.
V1 was towed from the scene due to damage.    The unrestrained driver of V1 was
fully ejected and sustained fatal injuries.
V1 was traveling southbound in the first lane of a two-lane roadway.  V1
departed the road to the right side, where its front impacted two trees.  V1
rotated clockwise and rolled two quarter-turns towards its left side, coming to
rest in a ditch on its top.
V1 was in the right lane of the two eastbound lanes of a four-lane road and
approaching a private drive.  V2 was traveling behind V1.  V3 was stopped in
lane one of the private drive heading south.  V2 began to slow and attempt to
turn right into the private drive.  The front of V1 contacted the right side of
V2 as V2 was turning right into the private drive.  V1 then continued and its
front contacted the left side of V3.  V1 and V3 both came to rest on the right
roadside.  V2 came to rest in its initial lane.
Vehicle one was traveling west while negotiating a left curve on a two-lane
roadway.  V1 departed its lane to the right and drove onto the right roadside.
The front of V1 contacted a tree causing V1 to rotate clockwise.  V1 came to
rest facing north while still on the roadside.    V1 was not equipped with air
bags.  V1 was towed from the crash scene due to disabling damage.    The driver
of V1 was reported as being restrained.  He did not sustain injury.  The front
right passenger of V1 was reported unrestrained.  He was ejected from the
vehicle during the sequence and sustained fatal injuries.
V1 was traveling northbound on a two-lane curving road.  V1 departed the road to
the left, then corrected right and departed the road to the right side.  On the
right roadside, the front of V1 ran over two small trees, then traversed a
ditch and impacted the opposite embankment.  V1's front then struck a copse of
five small trees.  V1 rotated clockwise and rolled two quarter-turns to its
left, coming to rest on the roadside on its top.
V1, eastbound hit a puddle of water, lost control entered a clockwise rotation,
tripped over to the left and rolled 5 quarter turns, coming to rest on the
driver side.
V1 was traveling a two-lane opposite direction roadway negotiating a curve. V1
lost control and departed the roadway to the left and entered a ditch and then
over turned and stuck some trees coming to rest off the roadway.     V1 was
towed from the scene due to damage.  One occupant was partially ejected and
received fatal injuries. The other occupant was fully ejected and air lifted to
a local trauma center.
V1 was traveling east in lane one of the two northbound lanes on a barrier
divided roadway.  V2 was traveling east in lane two of the same roadway.  V1
hydroplaned and crossed the center lane line.  The left rear of V1 contacted the
right front of V2.  V1 then rotated counterclockwise and crossed the left lane
and went head on into the median.  The front of V1 contacted the median wall.
V2 went left into the median wall and contacted the wall with its front left
corner.    V1 was not equipped with air bags.  V2 was equipped with dual frontal
air bags that both deployed.  V1 was towed from the crash scene, however, it
did not sustain disabling damage.  V2 was towed from the crash scene due to
disabling damage.    The restrained driver of V1 did not sustain injury.  The
restrained driver of V2 did not sustain injury.  The restrained front right
passenger of V2 sustained injury.  She was transported to a local hospital for
treatment.
V1 was traveling northbound in lane one when a large truck in lane two came over
into lane one. V1 hit the brakes and steered left to avoid the truck and lost
control and struck the bridge rail on the left side and then the vehicle turned
over and came to final rest on its top in the median area past the bridge.    V1
was equipped with dual frontal air bags neither of which deployed during the
accident. The vehicle was towed from the scene due to damage.
V1 was traveling east in lane one of the two northbound lanes when V1 drifted
onto the right roadside.  The driver of V1 steered left and braked causing the
wells to lock.  V1 was stuck in a counterclockwise yaw.  V1 contacted a sign
with its front plan.  V1 then continued to skid and rotate.  V1 skidded across a
private drive then into a ditch.  V1 fell into the ditch causing V1 to roll
with its right plan leading.  V1 continued to roll as it exited the ditch.  V1
contacted a pole (unknown plane of contact) then crossed another private drive.
V1 contacted another post (unknown plane of contact).  V1 then rolled into
another ditch where it came to rest on its wheels.  The unrestrained rear
passengers were all ejected from the vehicle during the crash sequence.    V1
was equipped with dual frontal air bags that did not deploy.  V1 was towed from
the crash sequence due to disabling damage.    The unrestrained driver, front
right, and right rear passenger of V1 were all transported from the scene to a
medical facility and hospitalized.  The unrestrained rear left and center
passengers sustained fatal injuries and died from their injuries.
V1 was traveling on a two-lane opposite direction roadway when he entered a
curve to the right. V1 lost control because of poor tire tread.  V1 departed the
roadway to the left and the front impacted a ditch and caused the vehicle to
roll over 4 quarter turns coming to final rest off the roadway to the left
facing in a westerly direction.    V1 was equipped with dual frontal air bags
neither of which deployed and dual roof side rail bags both of which deployed.
V1 was also equipped with dual seat back air bags of which only the driver's

vehicle two deflected off the north roadside and came to rest facing southeast.
Both vehicles were towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling north approaching the top of a steep hill. After
topping the hill and beginning the downhill grade, the driver lost control of
the vehicle and went off the left side of the road. The vehicle went down an
embankment and the front contacted an embankment.  V1 then impacted a large
tree. Vehicle one rotated counterclockwise and rolled over one-quarter turn with
the right side leading.  While on its right side, V1 impacted several more
trees with its top plane before coming to final rest headed north. Vehicle one
was at the bottom of the embankment and in a ditch at final rest. This vehicle
was equipped with Certified Advanced 208 Compliant frontal air bags, both of
which deployed in the crash. Vehicle one was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was a motorcycle traveling west in the second lane approaching a
four-legged intersection controlled by a traffic signal.  Vehicle two was
traveling south turning left at the same intersection to go east on a two lane
one way street.  As vehicle two turned left the motorcycle swerved into the
third lane.  As both vehicles entered the intersection the motorcycle contacted
the left plane of vehicle two. The driver of vehicle one was thrown off the
motorcycle and contacted the left front wheel and the hood on vehicle two.  Both
vehicles stopped at impact.  Vehicle one was facing west and vehicle two was
facing southeast at final rest.  The driver of vehicle one was killed in the
crash.
Vehicle one was traveling south, in lane one negotiating a curve to the right.
Vehicle two was traveling north, in lane two negotiating a curve to the left.
Vehicle three was traveling north, in lane one negotiating a curve to the left.
As Vehicle one crossed over into the northbound lanes its frontal plane
contacted Vehicle two's left plane. Post impact with Vehicle two, Vehicle one
continued southeast where its frontal plane contacted Vehicle three's left
plane. Post impact with Vehicle three, Vehicle one continued southeast and
departed the roadway where its left front tire contacted a curb, Post impact
with the curb, Vehicle one continued off of the roadway where its frontal plane
contacted a stop sign, phone box and a power pole. Vehicle one came to final
rest at impact with the power pole facing southeast. Post impact with Vehicle
one, Vehicle two slightly rotated counterclockwise and was then impacted in the
rear plane by Vehicle three's frontal plane also causing sideswiping type damage
down the right side. Vehicle two came to final rest blocking lane two of the
northbound lanes, facing north. Post impact with Vehicle two, Vehicle three came
to final rest blocking lane one of the northbound lanes facing north. Vehicle
three then pulled off of the roadway to the right. Vehicle one and Vehicle two
were towed due to damage. Vehicle three was not towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling east in a left curve when the vehicle departed the
right road edge.  The right plane contacted a group of three trees.  The vehicle
rotated violently in a clockwise direction and the left front quarter panel
contacted another tree while the left rear quarter panel contacted a street
sign.  The left plane contacted another tree where the vehicle stopped facing
northwest.  The vehicle was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling east, crossing the southbound lanes of a seven-lane
divided roadway to turn left and go north. Vehicle two was traveling south in
lane three of the seven-lane roadway. There were no traffic control devices for
Vehicle two and Vehicle one had entered the roadway from an alley controlled by
a stop sign. As Vehicle one crossed the southbound lanes, its left was contacted
by the front of Vehicle two. Vehicle one rotated clockwise and came to rest
headed southeast and blocking lanes two and three of the southbound lanes.
Vehicle two continued southeast and came to rest headed south in the crossover
area and partially blocking lane three of the southbound lanes. Vehicle two was
towed due to disabling damage. Vehicle one was towed due to damage per the
police report.
Vehicle one was traveling west in lane two of an interstate roadway when the
right rear tire blew out causing vehicle ones' driver to lose control and depart
the left roadside into the median in a counterclockwise rotation. Upon entering
the median, vehicle one's right side tires dug into the ground causing vehicle
one to roll over with its right side leading 4 (four) quarter turns before
coming to rest upright facing south. Vehicle one was towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south, negotiating a sharp curve to the left. Vehicle
one departed the west road edge where it contacted and vaulted over a ditch,
then had a front corner impact with a tree, rotated counterclockwise, tripped
and rolled right an unknown number of quarter turns, then came to rest on the
right side facing back toward the roadway.  While V1 was inverted, it had a left
side event with a second tree.    Vehicle one was towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling north negotiating a curve to the left went it drifted
off the right road edge. The driver steered back left crossing the southbound
lanes of traffic then apparently attempted to steer back right just prior to
departing the left roadside. Vehicle one began to rotate clockwise as it went
down an embankment just prior to impacting a tree with its left plane. Vehicle
one came to rest off the left roadside facing northeast and was towed due to
damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south in lane one of the interstate roadway. Vehicle
two was traveling north in lane one of the same roadway. The north and south
lanes were divided by a grass median. Vehicle one went off the left side of the
road and into the median. After crossing the median, Vehicle one re-entered the
roadway in the northbound lanes. The right side of Vehicle one contacted the
front of Vehicle two. Vehicle one rotated counterclockwise and Vehicle two
rotated clockwise. The right back of Vehicle one contacted the left back of
Vehicle two. Both vehicles continued off the roadway and onto the grassy
roadside where Vehicle came to rest headed west and Vehicle two came to rest
headed northwest. Both vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was stopped northbound in lane four. Vehicle two was southbound in
lane three. Vehicle three was stopped eastbound in lane one. V1 entered the
intersection turning left and the front struck the front of V2. V2 traveled to
the southwest and the front struck the left side of V3. V1 and V2 were towed due
to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling north, negotiating a curve to the right. Vehicle one
departed the west road edge. The driver of Vehicle one overcorrected back to the
east and departed the east road edge while rotating counterclockwise.  Vehicle
one's right plane contacted a tree. Vehicle one deflected off the tree, rotated
clockwise, and began to rollover with its left plane leading. Vehicle one came
to final rest on its top plane facing east. Vehicle one was towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south on an interstate roadway in the second lane when
it departed the left road edge into the grass median in a clockwise yaw.  The
vehicle rolled over to the left ten quarter-turns coming to final rest on the
top plane facing north in the median.  The belted driver was killed in the crash
and the vehicle was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling east negotiating a left curve when it entered the
westbound lane of traffic. Vehicle one then steered right to avoid a non-contact
vehicle where it then departed the right roadside. Vehicle one then impacted a
plastic gas line marker with its frontal plane. Post impact with the gas marker,
vehicle one then impacted a large tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle one then
rotated clockwise and came to rest in the roadway facing south. Post impact
with the tree, V1s' engine compartment caught fire from the battery. Vehicle one
was towed due to damage. V1's right rear occupant, restrained with lap and
shoulder belts, was pronounced dead at the scene.
Vehicle one was traveling north, going downhill while negotiating a right curve.
The vehicle went over the centerline and then off the right side of the road.
Upon re-entering the roadway, the driver lost control and the vehicle began to
rotate counterclockwise while moving towards the left road edge. After leaving
the left side of the road, Vehicle one began to rollover with the right side
leading. The vehicle rolled two (2) quarter-turns. While on the top plane, V1
contacted a large tree. Vehicle one came to rest still off the roadway and
headed southeast with the top plane in contact with the ground. The vehicle was
towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south, negotiating a left curve when it went off the
right side of the road. After traveling some distance on the roadside, the front
of the vehicle contacted a drainage culvert. The vehicle began to rotate
clockwise and rollover with the left side leading. Vehicle one rolled two (2)
quarter-turns and came to rest with the top plane in contact with the ground.
The heading for Vehicle one at final rest was southwest. The vehicle was towed
due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south on a two lane straight road when it departed the
left road edge and entered a ditch.  The vehicle impacted a culvert and
re-entered the roadway where it rolled over with the left side leading five
quarter turns.  Vehicle one came to final rest on the left plane facing west on
the road.  The vehicle was only equipped with a driver airbag which did not
deploy in the crash and the vehicle was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south in lane two, negotiating a curve to the right.
Vehicle two was traveling north in lane one, negotiating a curve to the left.
Vehicle one crossed over into the northbound lanes where its frontal plane
contacted Vehicles two's frontal plane. Post impact with Vehicle two, Vehicle
one was pushed backwards coming to final rest blocking lanes one and two of the
southbound lanes, facing east. Post impact with Vehicle one, Vehicle two
continued northwest coming to final rest blocking lanes one and two of the
northbound lanes, facing northwest. Both vehicles were towed due to damage.
Vehicle one had an FSN issued for non-deployment of the driver air bag.
V1 was traveling westbound on a two-lane road, curving right. V1 departed the
road to the left side, where the front of V1 impacted a tree.  V1 rotated
counter-clockwise from impact and rolled two quarter-turns towards its right
side.  V1 came to rest on its roof on the roadside.
Vehicle one was traveling southeast approaching an intersection, intending to
turn left. Vehicle two was traveling northwest approaching the same
intersection. As vehicle one attempted to turn left, its front plane impacted
the front plane of vehicle two. Both vehicles deflected northeast to final rest.
The crash occurred on at a four legged intersection.  Vehicle one was traveling
west and turning left at the intersection.  Vehicle two was traveling east going
straight through the intersection.  The front of vehicle two contacted the
right plane of vehicle one.  Vehicle one rotated counterclockwise and departed
the right road edge to come to final rest facing west.  Vehicle two also rotated
counterclockwise and came to final rest off the road on the left side facing
east.  Both vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.  The front driver and
passenger airbags deployed in both vehicles.
V1 was traveling westbound on a divided highway.  V1 departed the road to the
right side, where the front of V1 impacted an embankment.  V1 traversed the
embankment and vaulted over a private drive.  On the opposite side of the drive,
V1 impacted another embankment, rotated clockwise and rolled four quarter-turns
towards its left side. V1 came to rest on its wheels on the roadside.
Vehicle one was traveling east on a westbound roadway in lane two negotiating a
slight curve to the left while going uphill when its frontal plane impacted the
frontal plane of vehicle two, which was traveling west in the same lane. Post
impact, vehicle one came to rest facing northeast and was towed due to damage.
Post impact, vehicle two came to rest facing southwest and was towed due to
damage. Vehicle two was a Certified 208 Compliant vehicle of which the driver's
frontal airbag deployed.
The crash occurred at an intersection controlled by a traffic light.  Vehicle
one was traveling west in the third lane approaching the intersection going
straight through.  Vehicle two was going east in the left turn lane.  As vehicle
two turned left the front of vehicle two contacted the left plane of vehicle
one.  Vehicle one then rotated clockwise and departed the right road edge where
the front struck a utility pole. Vehicle one came to final rest facing north at
the pole.  Vehicle two rotated counterclockwise to final rest facing north in
the westbound lanes.
Vehicle one was traveling east in the lane four, (the left turn lane). Vehicle
two was traveling west in lane three. Vehicle one turned left and its front
contacted the front of Vehicle two. Vehicle one rotated counterclockwise and
moved southwest where it came to rest headed southwest in the crossover area of
the roadway. Vehicle two moved northwest where it came to rest headed northwest
and partially blocking the northwest corner of the intersection. Both vehicles
were towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling east in lane three approaching an intersection
controlled by a traffic light. Vehicle two (towing a small trailer) was
traveling north in lane two, turning left at the same intersection. As Vehicle
two made the left turn, the front of Vehicle one contacted the left side of
Vehicle two. Vehicle one came to rest blocking the intersection still headed
east. Vehicle two came to rest also blocking the intersection and still headed
north. Both vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling east, in lane one going straight. Vehicle one was
towing a trailer with lawn equipment. Vehicle two was traveling east, in lane
two going straight. Vehicle three was traveling east, in lane three going
straight. Vehicle one began to slide on wet roads and V1 impacted the curb with
its front.  Deflecting off the curb, the front of V2 struck the left side of V1.
Post impact with Vehicle two, Vehicle one then contacted Vehicle two in its
right plane with its left plane in a sideslap. Post impact with Vehicle one,
Vehicle two with its left plane contacted Vehicle three in its frontal plane.
Vehicle one came to final rest blocking lane two, facing east. Vehicle two came
to final rest blocking lane three, facing northeast. Vehicle three came to final
rest at impact with Vehicle two, facing east. All three Vehicles were towed due
to damage.
The crash occurred at a four-legged intersection controlled with a traffic
signal.  Vehicle one was traveling east in the right lane going straight through
the intersection.  Vehicle two was travelling south crossing through the
intersection also.  The front of vehicle one contacted the right plane of
vehicle two.  Vehicle one came to a stop at impact.  Vehicle two rotated
counterclockwise and came to final rest off the left side of the road in a
parking lot facing southeast.  Both vehicles were reported as towed due to
disabling damage.  No airbags deployed in either vehicle.
Vehicle one was traveling north negotiating a curve to the right when it
departed the left roadside. Upon departing the roadway, vehicle one impacted a
tree with its frontal plane. Vehicle one rotated counterclockwise slightly
coming to rest facing west. During the impact, vehicle one experienced a fire
event in the engine compartment, which fully engulfed the vehicle. The driver
was pronounced dead at the scene.
Vehicle one and Vehicle two were traveling south in lane one of the interstate
roadway approaching an exit ramp. Vehicle two was in front of Vehicle one.
Vehicle two moved onto the exit ramp and began to slow down. Vehicle one moved
onto the exit ramp at a higher speed. The front of Vehicle one contacted the
back of Vehicle two. Vehicle one began to rotate clockwise while still traveling
south. Vehicle one came to rest headed north, just south of the exit ramp, in
the painted warning area. Vehicle two rotated clockwise and moved west (to the

lanes. Both vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.
V1 was traveling eastbound on a five-lane roadway.  V1 departed the road to the
right, where the front of V1 impacted a wooden utility pole.  V1 rotated
clockwise and came to rest on the roadside.
Vehicle one was traveling West negotiating a curve to the left when it drifted
off the right road shoulder. Vehicle one then steered left crossing the roadway
and departed the left roadside. Vehicle one then attempted to steer back right
but began to roll over with the left side leading. Vehicle one rolled over four

towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling west. Vehicle one departed the north road edge where
its front plane contacted a large tree stump. Vehicle one came to final rest on

V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two-lane, two-way roadway.
V2 was traveling southbound in the opposing lane.  V1 moved left into the
southbound lane, where the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.  V1 rotated
counter-clockwise from impact and departed the road to the right side, where V1
rolled four quarter-turns towards its right side.
Vehicle one was traveling west negotiating a right curve while going downhill.
The vehicle crossed the centerline and then went off the left side of the road.
After traveling some distance on the roadside, the vehicle became airborne,
jumped a ravine and the front contacted an embankment on the far side of the
ravine. The vehicle then rolled two (2) quarter-turns to the left before coming
to final rest with the top plane in contact with the ground. The driver was

Vehicle one was stopped northbound in lane one. Vehicle two was westbound in
lane two. V1 entered the intersection and the right side was struck by the front
of V2. V1 rotated clockwise, traveled to the northwest and the right side
struck a small pole. V2 traveled to the northwest and the front struck a small
movable sign. Both vehicles were towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling east on a two lane left curve road when the right
wheels dropped off the right edge of the road.  The driver over corrected by
steering left and lost control of the vehicle.  Vehicle one departed the left
road edge and the front contacted a small bush, then a chain link fence and a
large tree.  Vehicle one rotated clockwise and the left plane contacted the
fence.  Vehicle one came to final rest with the left side against the fence
facing south.  This vehicle is equipped with frontal Certified Advanced 208
Compliant airbags, of which the driver's side deployed.  The vehicle was towed
due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south when the vehicle went off the right side of the
road. After leaving the roadway, vehicle one went down a slight embankment where
the front and undercarriage contacted the ground. The vehicle spun around
clockwise and came to rest headed north still on the grassy roadside. The
vehicle was towed but no disabling damage was found on the vehicle.
The crash occurred on a four lane interstate roadway with a grass median.  There
was a guardrail along the inside and outside edge of the northbound lanes.
Vehicle one was traveling north in the second lane.  The driver experienced a
seizure causing the vehicle to depart the left road edge. The left plane
contacted the inside guardrail.  The vehicle rotated clockwise and the rear
plane contacted the guardrail.  The passenger grabbed the steering wheel and
steered the vehicle to an exit ramp and stopped it with the emergency brake
facing north.  None of the airbags deployed and the police reported the vehicle
as towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling east, in lane three going straight. Vehicle one
steered right to avoid a non-contact dump truck that was entering the road from
the left. Vehicle one then steered left and departed the north road edge to the
left into the median where its frontal plane contacted a guardrail. Post impact
with the guardrail, Vehicle one began to rollover with its left plane leading
six (6) quarter turns. Vehicle one continued to contact the guardrail as it
rolled over non-horizontally. Vehicle one came to final rest on its top plane
facing east. The driver of Vehicle one was fully ejected. Vehicle one was towed
due to damage.
V1 was traveling northbound in the first lane of a two-lane, divided interstate
highway.  V1 departed the road to the right side, where the right side of V1

its left side and came to rest with the right plane in contact with the ground.
During the rollover, the driver and right front passenger were completely
ejected.  The right rear occupant was seated in a booster seat and was not
injured.
Vehicle one was traveling east in the left turn lane (lane four) at an
intersection controlled by a traffic light. Vehicle two was traveling east in
lane two of the same roadway approaching the same intersection. Vehicle three
was traveling south in the right turn lane, stopped at a yield sign for traffic.
As Vehicle one turned left, the front of Vehicle two contacted the right side
of Vehicle one. Vehicle one rotated clockwise while moving northwest where its
back plane contacted the left plane of Vehicle three. Vehicle one continued
northwest and came to rest partially blocking the right turn lane of the

left plane of V3.  V2 came to rest on the west side of the intersection heading

lane of the northbound lanes. All three vehicles were towed due to disabling
damage.
Vehicle one was traveling west crossing through a traffic light controlled
intersection when its' front plane came into contact with the left plane of
vehicle two, a large Non-CDS semi tractor-trailer which was traveling south

came to rest in the intersection facing south. Post impact, V2 came to a

towed due to police reported damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south going straight. Vehicle one drifted off of the
roadway onto the west shoulder. The driver of Vehicle one attempted to guide the
vehicle back onto the roadway by steering left. Vehicle one then crossed over
into the northbound lane and departed the east shoulder. The driver of Vehicle
one attempted to guide the vehicle back onto the roadway by steering right. The
left side tires caught the edge of the road causing the vehicle to rollover nine
(9) quarter turns with its left plane leading. Vehicle one rolled over and slid
across the roadway coming to final rest off of the west shoulder facing west on
its left plane. Vehicle one was towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling west merging onto an interstate roadway.  Vehicle one
attempted to merge from lane one to lane two, however there was a non-contact
tractor trailer rig traveling west in lane two so in an attempt to avoid a
collision vehicle one steered right and departed the right roadside. After
departing the roadway, vehicle one impacted a drainage ditch with its frontal
plane. Post impact with the ditch, vehicle one rolled over with its left plane
leading two quarter turns coming to rest on its top plane facing northwest.
Vehicle one was towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south, negotiating a left curve on a temporary
construction drive and approaching an intersection to turn left. Vehicle two was
traveling west, in lane one going straight through the intersection. As Vehicle
two passed through the intersection the frontal plane contacted the left plane
of Vehicle one. Post impact with Vehicle two, Vehicle one rotated clockwise
coming to final rest facing west, blocking lane one of the westbound roadway.
Post impact with Vehicle one, Vehicle two rotated counterclockwise coming to
final rest facing southwest, blocking lane one and two of the westbound roadway.
Vehicle two was a 208 Certified Compliant vehicle that the driver's frontal air
bag deployed. The police reported Vehicle one was towed due to damage. Vehicle
two was towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling west in the second lane turning left at a traffic
signal controlled intersection.  Vehicle two was traveling east in the second
lane and as vehicle one turned left the front contacted the front of vehicle
two.  Vehicle one was pushed backwards after the initial impact and its back
plane contacted the front plane of vehicle three that was traveling west just
behind vehicle one.  Vehicle one came to final rest in the intersection facing
southwest.  Vehicle two came to final rest in the second eastbound lane in the
intersection facing east.  Vehicle three came to final rest in the second
westbound lane facing west.  No airbags deployed in vehicles one and three.  The
frontal airbags in vehicle two deployed.  All three vehicles were towed due to
disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south, in lane three going straight. Vehicle two was
stopped in lane three in front of Vehicle one. The front of Vehicle one
contacted the rear of Vehicle two.
Vehicles one and two were both traveling north in lane two of an interstate
roadway. Vehicle one was in front of Vehicle two when a magnetic sign came off
of Vehicle one and struck the windshield of Vehicle two. The vehicles continued
up the road for approximately three (3) miles before coming to final rest on the
right shoulder of the roadway still headed north. Vehicle one was not contacted
in the crash event and was not towed. Vehicle two was towed due to police
reported damage.
Vehicle one was traveling north at night on an unlit roadway. Three (3) horses
came onto the roadway from the west (the driver's left) and began crossing in
front of Vehicle one. The front of the vehicle contacted two (2) of the horses
causing the horses to fall onto the hood and top of the vehicle. Vehicle one
then moved northwest and off the roadway where the undercarriage contacted a
decomposing tree stump. The vehicle came to rest in a wooded area headed
northwest. The horses were fatally injured and came to rest in the roadway. The
vehicle was towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south on a two lane left curved road.  The vehicle
departed the left road edge in a counterclockwise rotation and the right plane
contacted an embankment.  The vehicle moved backwards to final rest in the grass
facing north.  The driver and right front passenger were transported with crash
related injuries.  The police reported that the vehicle was towed due to damage
and the driver's airbag reportedly deployed.
V1 was traveling southbound on a two-lane roadway.  V2 was traveling in the
opposite direction.  V1 moved to its left and entered the northbound lane, where
the front of V1 impacted the front of V2.  Both vehicles rotated clockwise, and
V1 departed the road into a ditch on the east roadside, where V1 rolled onto
its left side, causing the top plane to contact the opposite slope of the
embankment.  V1 came upright as it went up the embankment and came to rest in
the ditch.  V2 departed the west roadside and caught fire.
Vehicle one was traveling south on an interstate roadway in the second lane when
it partially departed the left road edge.  The driver overcorrected, steering
right, and crossed both southbound lanes departing the right road edge.  The
vehicle rotated counterclockwise and the right plane struck a tree.  The vehicle
then rotated clockwise and came to final rest facing north on the grassy
roadside.  Occupant four in the second row was fully ejected from the vehicle
through the second row right side glazing.  Occupant seven in the third row was
fully ejected through the third row right side glazing.  The vehicle was towed
due to disabling damage.  Occupant three in the second row left-most seat was
restrained by a child safety seat.
Vehicle one was traveling south. Vehicle one went off the right side of the
roadway where its frontal plane contacted a tree. Vehicle one came to final rest
at impact facing southwest.
V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane of a two-lane, divided highway.
V2, a large truck, was abreast of V1 in the first lane.  V1 drifted to its left,
then corrected right, where the right side of V1 impacted the left-rear tandem
wheels of the truck's trailer.  V1 veered left again and departed the road to
the left side as it rotated counter-clockwise.  In the unpaved median, V1 rolled
four quarter-turns towards its right side.  V1 came to rest on its wheels in
the median.
Vehicle one was traveling north in lane one, negotiating a curve to the right.
Vehicle one departed the roadway to the right where its frontal plane contacted
a signpost. Post impact with the signpost, Vehicle one began to rotate clockwise
and began to rollover with its left plane leading four (4) quarter turns.
Vehicle one came to final rest on its wheels facing northeast. Police reported
that Vehicle one was towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was southbound in lane one. Vehicle two was northbound in lane one.
V1 turned left in an intersection and the front struck the front of V2. Both
vehicles were towed due to damage.
This multi-vehicle crash occurred at a four-legged intersection with the
north/south roadway being controlled by a stop sign.  Vehicle one was traveling
north approaching the intersection.  Vehicle two was traveling east and vehicle
three was traveling west approaching the intersection.  As vehicle one entered
the intersection to turn left the front contacted the right plane of vehicle
two.  Vehicle two rotated clockwise into the westbound lane in front of vehicle
three.  The front of vehicle three contacted the left plane of vehicle two.
This acted as a trip point for vehicle two and it rolled with the left side
leading across the top plane of vehicle three.  Vehicle one came to final rest
on the east leg of the intersection partially off the north edge of the road
facing east.  Vehicle two came to final rest on its wheels on the east leg of
the intersection facing south across the westbound lane.  Vehicle three came to
final rest on the west side of the intersection off the south road edge facing
southwest.  The driver of vehicle three was killed in the crash.  All three
vehicles were towed due to disabling damage.  The frontal airbags deployed in
vehicle one.  There was an occupied child safety seat in the second row of
vehicle two.
Vehicle one and Vehicle two were both traveling west in lane two. Vehicle two
was stopped at an intersection controlled by a traffic light. Vehicle one was
approaching the same intersection behind Vehicle two. The front of Vehicle one
contacted the back of Vehicle two. Vehicle one moved west-northwest and came to
rest headed west and partially blocking the northwest area of the intersection.
Vehicle two moved west and came to rest headed west and blocking lane one of the
westbound lanes. Both vehicles were reported as towed due to disabling damage.
Vehicle one was on a narrow two way street with no lane lanes going east
attempting to turn left onto a two-lane north/south roadway when its left plane
was contacted by the frontal plane of vehicle two, which was traveling south.
Post initial impact, vehicle one's left plane side slapped the right plane of
vehicle two. Vehicle one then departed the east roadside where it impacted some
small saplings with its right plane before coming to rest facing north. Vehicle
two came to rest off the east roadside facing east. Both vehicles were towed due
to damage.
Vehicle one was traveling south, in lane one going straight through a
three-legged intersection, controlled by a traffic signal. Vehicle two was
traveling east, in lane two a left turn lane, making a left turn at the same
intersection. As Vehicle two passed through the intersection the front plane of
Vehicle one contacted the left plane of Vehicle two. Vehicle one came to final
rest blocking the intersection facing south. Post impact with Vehicle one,
Vehicle two rotated counterclockwise coming to final rest facing west, blocking
the intersection. Both Vehicles were towed due to damage.
Vehicle one was exiting a parking lot intending to cross two westbound lanes,

V1 was southbound, V2 was eastbound, both approaching an intersection. Both
vehicles entered the intersection, V1 impacted V2's left side with its front
end.  V1's right plane and V2's left plane side slapped. V2 was towed due to
damage.  No one was transported to a medical facility.
Vehicle 1 was headed west on a divided seven lane street.  Vehicle 1 was in the

to damage.  The passenger inside vehicle 1 was killed in the crash..
V1 was northbound, approaching an intersection, intending to go straight.  V2

V1 impacted V2's right side with its front end within the intersection.  V2

was transported to a trauma center and admitted.
Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, left curving roadway in lane one.
As the vehicle approached the left curve of the roadway it continued off the
edge of the road on the right side where its front impacted a tree.  The vehicle
came to rest just right of the tree.  The vehicle was towed due to damage.  The
driver was transported and admitted to a trauma center.
Vehicle 1 was headed east rounding a curve when the vehicle left the left side
of the roadway.  The vehicle struck a mailbox and stop sign before crossing the

The vehicle continued east in the yard striking a brick tree ring and then

rest.  The vehicle was towed due to damage.  The vehicle was equipped with
frontal airbags, side airbags and side curtains that did not deploy in the
crash.
V1 and V2 were both westbound.  Driver of V2 apparently had a seizure, lost
control and impacted the concrete barrier on the right side of the roadway.  V2
crossed towards the south impacting V1, causing it to enter a clockwise yaw.
Both vehicles entered an exit ramp, V1 still in a yaw, when V2 impacted V1's

separating.  V1 made numerous tire contacts and a left side impact with the

end.  It passed through the fence and entered another roadway, coming to rest

V1 was traveling southbound and approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling
eastbound and approaching the same intersection.  In the intersection, the front

V1 departed the road over the southeast corner and impacted a signpost and a

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a seven lane, median divided roadway in lane

intersecting five lane roadway in lane two, also passing through the

side of vehicle 1.  Vehicle 1's left plane and vehicle 2's right plane then

The vehicle, pulling a trailer, was westbound when it departed the roadway to

The vehicle rolled left onto its roof, then back onto its left side. It came to

towed due to damage. No one was injured.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a two lane left curving roadway.  The vehicle
moved to the left where its front impacted a parked vehicle's left side.
Vehicle 1 continued south where it came to rest.  Vehicle 1 was towed from the
scene.  No injuries were reported.
Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a two lane, downhill roadway.  Vehicle 1 went
off road to the right and its front impacted a tree.  The vehicle came to rest
at the tree.  The vehicle was towed from the scene due to damage and the driver
was transported for injuries.
V1 was traveling westbound in the second lane (two-way left turn lane) of a
three-lane roadway, approaching an intersection.  V2 was traveling westbound in

V1 was northbound on a one-way roadway approaching an intersection.  V2 was

Vehicle 1 and 2 were both headed south on a four lane undivided street.  Vehicle

V1 was traveling westbound on a curved roadway.  V1 departed the road to the

Both vehicles were towed due to damage.  The driver of V1 was treated and
released at a trauma center.  The driver of V2 was admitted to the trauma

Vehicle 1 was traveling east on a three lane roadway, passing through the

V1 was westbound stopped, due to backed up traffic at an intersection.  V2 was

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a 7 lane, median divided roadway in lane four,

Vehicle 1 came to rest in the intersection and vehicle 2 rotated clockwise and

Vehicle 1 was headed south on a six lane median divided street, traveling in the

Vehicle 1 was traveling north on a two lane, non divided roadway in lane one,

Vehicle one (V1) was eastbound in lane two. Vehicle two (V2) was westbound in

V1 was traveling westbound in the first lane of a two-lane roadway.  V2 was

V1 was eastbound when it departed the roadway to the left.  V2 was traveling

The vehicle was headed east when it departed the roadway to the left and

Vehicle 1 was traveling west on a three lane roadway, passing through an

Vehicle 1 was headed north on a six-lane median divided street, in the third

Vehicle 1 was headed east on a two lane undivided street.  Vehicle 2 was headed

V1 was traveling east, approaching an intersection, intending to turn left.  V2

Vehicle 1 was traveling south on a three lane, sagging, one way roadway in lane

Vehicle 1 was traveling south approaching an intersection.  Vehicle 2 was

Vehicle 1 was headed east on a two lane undivided street.  The vehicle moved
into the westbound lane.  The driver swerved to avoid a westbound vehicle and

The vehicle was towed due to damage.
Vehicle 1 was traveling south.  It came to an intersection and turned right to

Vehicle 1 was traveling west and turned south on a five lane undivided street.

The vehicle was northbound approaching a "T" "end departure" intersection.  The
